message.content:
Purple is generally regarded as a color representing wealth, nobility, and power. It has been associated with royalty throughout history because in ancient times the dye used to make purple clothes was extremely expensive and rare, so only the wealthiest and most powerful people could afford it. Today, this association with luxury and extravagance continues.

Purple also symbolizes creativity, wisdom, peace, ambition, spirituality, devotion and magic. In some spiritual practices or beliefs systems like chakras (energy centers) purple represents enlightenment or higher state of consciousness due to its placement at the top level as crown chakra.
